#align expression & metadata
#tanspose expression: samples as rows
X_all = expr.T.copy()
X_all.index = X_all.index.astype(str)

# metadata preparing
meta = meta.copy()
meta.index = meta.index.astype(str)
# Target label
label_col = "pam50 subtype:ch1"

#only samples that appear in both datasets
common_samples = X_all.index.intersection(meta.index)

# Subset both datasets
X_all = X_all.loc[common_samples]
y_all = meta.loc[common_samples, label_col].astype(str)

print("Final X shape:", X_all.shape)
print("Final y shape:", y_all.shape)
print("Number of matched samples:", len(common_samples))

# Knee heuristic op basis v d elbow het aantal pca's voor model kiezen
def pick_knee(cumvar_array):
    if len(cumvar_array) < 3:
        return 2
    dv = np.diff(cumvar_array)
    ddv = np.diff(dv)
    knee_idx = int(np.argmin(ddv) + 2)  # +2 because diff shifts
    return max(2, knee_idx)

n_comp_80 = int(np.searchsorted(cumvar, 0.80) + 1) if cumvar[-1] >= 0.80 else max_possible
n_comp_knee = pick_knee(cumvar)
n_components = max(5, min(n_comp_knee, n_comp_80, max_possible))
print("n_comp_80:", n_comp_80, "| n_comp_knee:", n_comp_knee, "| selected:", n_components)

n_comp_80: 163 | n_comp_knee: 3 | selected: 5

# ---------- 3. Fit PCA with chosen n_components and transform ----------
pca = PCA(n_components=n_components, random_state=RND)
pca.fit(X_train)

X_train_pcs = pd.DataFrame(pca.transform(X_train),
                           index=X_train.index,
                           columns=[f"PC{i+1}" for i in range(n_components)])
X_test_pcs  = pd.DataFrame(pca.transform(X_test),
                           index=X_test.index,
                           columns=[f"PC{i+1}" for i in range(n_components)])

print("X_train_pcs shape:", X_train_pcs.shape, "X_test_pcs shape:", X_test_pcs.shape)

# Quick PCA 2D plot (train)
plt.figure(figsize=(7,6))
sns.scatterplot(x=X_train_pcs["PC1"], y=X_train_pcs["PC2"], hue=y_train, alpha=0.6, s=30)
plt.title("Train PCA (PC1 vs PC2) colored by PAM50")
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05,1), loc='upper left')
plt.show()

# ---------- 4. Define models + small hyperparameter grids ----------
models = {
    "RandomForest": (
        RandomForestClassifier(random_state=RND, class_weight="balanced"),
        {"n_estimators":[250], "max_depth":[10, None]}
    ),
    "SVM": (
        SVC(probability=True, random_state=RND),
        {"C":[1,10], "kernel":["rbf"]}
    ),
    "LogReg": (
        LogisticRegression(max_iter=2000, solver="saga", multi_class="multinomial", random_state=RND),
        {"C":[0.1,1,10]}
    )
}

cv = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=RND)
best_estimators = {}
In [29]:
# ---------- 5. GridSearchCV on TRAIN (balanced_accuracy) ----------
for name, (estimator, param_grid) in models.items():
    print("Training grid for:", name)
    gs = GridSearchCV(estimator, param_grid, cv=cv, scoring="balanced_accuracy", n_jobs=-1, verbose=0)
    gs.fit(X_train_pcs, y_train)
    best_estimators[name] = gs.best_estimator_
    print(f" {name} best CV balanced_accuracy: {gs.best_score_:.4f} | best_params: {gs.best_params_}")

# ---------- 6. Evaluate on TEST ----------
for name, est in best_estimators.items():
    print("\n=== EVALUATION:", name, "===")
    y_pred = est.predict(X_test_pcs)
    print("Balanced accuracy:", balanced_accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, zero_division=0))
    classes = np.unique(np.concatenate([y_test.unique(), y_pred]))
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred, labels=classes)
    cm_df = pd.DataFrame(cm, index=classes, columns=classes)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,5))
    sns.heatmap(cm_df, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap="Blues")
    plt.title(f"Confusion Matrix: {name}")
    plt.ylabel("True")
    plt.xlabel("Pred")
    plt.show()

#modellen overfitten of underfitten
from sklearn.model_selection import learning_curve

def plot_learning_curve(estimator, X, y, title="Learning Curve"):
    train_sizes, train_scores, val_scores = learning_curve(
        estimator, X, y, cv=cv, scoring="balanced_accuracy", n_jobs=-1
    )
    train_scores_mean = train_scores.mean(axis=1)
    val_scores_mean = val_scores.mean(axis=1)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(5,7))
    plt.plot(train_sizes, train_scores_mean, label="Training score")
    plt.plot(train_sizes, val_scores_mean, label="Validation score")
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel("Training size")
    plt.ylabel("Balanced Accuracy")
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

for name, est in best_estimators.items():
    plot_learning_curve(est, X_train_pcs, y_train, title=f"Learning Curve: {name}")

#evaluatie v d verschillende modellen 
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score

results = []

for name, est in best_estimators.items():
    y_pred = est.predict(X_test_pcs)
    bal_acc = balanced_accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    f1_macro = f1_score(y_test, y_pred, average='macro', zero_division=0)
    results.append({"Model": name, "Balanced Accuracy": bal_acc, "F1 Macro": f1_macro})

results_df = pd.DataFrame(results).sort_values(by="Balanced Accuracy", ascending=False)
print(results_df)

# Visualisatie
plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
sns.barplot(x="Balanced Accuracy", y="Model", data=results_df, palette="viridis")
plt.title("Vergelijking van modellen op testset")
plt.xlim(0,1)
plt.show()

# rf.feature_importances_ geeft per PC de importance

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

# RandomForest importances per PC
pc_importances = rf.feature_importances_

# PCA-componenten matrix: rows = PCs, columns = originele features
pca_components = pca.components_  

# Gewicht per originele feature = sum over PCs van (PC importance * PC coefficient)
original_feature_importance = np.abs(pca_components.T @ pc_importances)

orig_feat_series = pd.Series(original_feature_importance, index=X_train.columns)
orig_feat_series.sort_values(ascending=False).plot(kind="bar", figsize=(50,4), title="Originele features gempacteerd via PCA")
plt.show()
